# Deploying {{ name }}

All deploy and flag operations go through `.ymir/deploy.py`. Run it from the project root.

## After making code changes

Once tests pass, deploy to dev:

```bash
python3 .ymir/deploy.py dev
```

## Feature flag lifecycle

```bash
# See current state
python3 .ymir/deploy.py status

# Turn a flag ON in dev (to test the feature)
python3 .ymir/deploy.py activate <flag>

# Turn a flag OFF in dev
python3 .ymir/deploy.py deactivate <flag>

# Dark-launch to prod (code ships, flags stay OFF)
python3 .ymir/deploy.py prod

# Release to users (flag ON in prod)
python3 .ymir/deploy.py release <flag>

# Rollback (flag OFF in prod)
python3 .ymir/deploy.py rollback <flag>
```

## Rules

- Never run `docker` commands directly.
- Never run `python3 ymir.py` — that tool lives outside this project.
- Always deploy to dev and verify before deploying to prod.
- New features must go behind a feature flag (see `feature_flags.yaml`).
